724062f-a.title: Manhattan: Washington Street - Morris Street
724062f-a.text:
Washington Street, east side, north fror above
Morris Street, showing buildings to the center of this
block that extend to Rector Street. At the right is
the Lebanon Bank at No. 59. This adjoins to the north,
the not shown St. Josephs R. C. Church (No. 57).
The Faour Bank is at No. 81-85. Tenements
to the north of the latter were subsequently demolished
and a 35-story office structure arected. This bears
Nos 91 Washington Street, 21 Rector Street, and 88
Greenwich Street.
June 11, 1929
P. L. Sperr
